  <description type="morphology">Stems 10–25 × 7–15 cm; ribs (13–)18–21; areoles (14–)21–26 mm apart along ribs;
        areolar glands present at least seasonally. Spines 13–24 per areole, pale yellow to grayish
        lavender to maroon; radial spines 9–16 per areole; abaxial (shortest) radial spine 6–19 ×
        (0.2–)0.4–0.6 mm; adaxial and lateral (longest) radial spines ca. 27–40 mm; central spines
        4–9 per areole, present at all ages, 27–41 × (0.7–)1.1–1.4 mm; longest central spine
        straight to strongly decurved; abaxial central spine porrect, ca. 27–40 mm Flowers 4–6.5 ×
        4–7.7 cm; inner tepals yellow or pink to magenta, basal portions blotched with maroon,
        2.5–3.7 × 1–1.8 cm; stigma lobes yellowish white to green. Fruits dehiscent only along
        single, longitudinal split, ± spheric, 17–18 mm. 2n = 22.</description>
