  <discussion>Echinomastus johnsonii varies geographically in both flower and spine color. The
        yellow-flowered plants have been named E. johnsonii var. lutescens. The pink-flowered plants
        occur in separate populations, as far as is known, to the north of the yellow-flowered
        plants, but the interface between the two forms is poorly understood.</discussion>
